title: Do You Fear the Wind?
creator: Hamlin Garland
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
description: LibriVox volunteers bring you 16 recordings of Do You Fear the Wind? by Hamlin Garland. This was the Weekly Poetry project for February 3, 2013. This poem is taken from An American Anthology, 1787–1900, Edmund Clarence Stedman, ed. (1833–1908). For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
subject: librivox; literature; audiobook; poetry; animals; advice; adventure; nature
